The Chief executive Officer of Monimichelle Group, Ebi Egbe and authorities in Cameroun have held talks on the way forward for the improvement of pitches being used at the on-going Africa Cup of Nations( AFCON) Cameroon 2021. Egbe whose outfit is Africa’s leading stadium facilities construction firm was invited by the Governor of Douala, Samuel Ivaha Diboua, disclosed that the meetings centred on how to make the pitches remain in good shape after the Nations Cup.   Young Lionesses arrive tomorrow for Falconets     NFF demands commitment, improved performance from referees     Rohr dismisses link with Black Stars   “The Cameroonian authorities are already looking at how to sustain the gains of hosting Africa’s biggest football fiesta,” hinted Egbe. “I am delighted that the job Monimichelle is doing is being recognized by other African countries. “ For us in Monimichelle the way to go is the construction of pitches that would outlive tournaments. We will bring our expertise to bear on this in Cameroun,” Egbe added. . He further disclosed that he has seen what the challenges are especially at the Japoma stadium in Douala, adding he was happy the local authorities are already looking at the way forward post AFCON.